  "prompt": "Would Fitbit charge 2 function in the artic circle at - 35 degree?",
  "response": "The Fitbit Charge 2 has certain operating temperature specifications. Typically, most consumer electronics have an operating temperature range that ensures functionality and prevents damage. For the Fitbit Charge 2, the safe operating temperature range is usually between -4\u00b0F (-20\u00b0C) and 113\u00b0F (45\u00b0C) according to the manufacturer's specifications.\n\nAt -35\u00b0C, it is significantly below the recommended operating temperature, which means the Fitbit Charge 2 would likely encounter problems functioning correctly. The extremely cold temperatures could impact battery performance, screen responsiveness, and other electronic components, potentially leading to device failure or permanent damage. Therefore, it's not advisable to use the Fitbit Charge 2 under such extreme conditions.",
